column10:
Percentage of Total Possible Score 
(out of 52.3)
column12: A01.EA The company made a public commitment to gender equality and women’s empowerment (e.g. signatory to the UN Women’s Empowerment Principles, or having made another public commitment at CEO level).
column14: A02.EA The company discloses one or more time-bound targets on gender equality and women’s empowerment with regard to its workplace.
column15: A02.EC The company discloses one or more time-bound targets on gender equality and women’s empowerment with regard  to its supply chain.
column16: A04. Gender-responsive human rights due diligence process
column17: A04.EA The company discloses what gender-related human rights impacts it has assessed and prioritised as being salient (i.e. most severe and potentially irremediable if not addressed).
column18: A04.EB The company consults with women or women's groups as part of the risk identification and assessment process.
column20: A05.EA The company has a gender-responsive mechanism through which employees can report grievances.
column21: A05.EB The company has one or more channel(s)/mechanism(s), or participates in a shared mechanism, accessible to all external individuals and communities who may be adversely impacted by the company (or individuals or organisations acting on their behalf or who are otherwise in a position to be aware of adverse impacts), to raise complaints or concerns.
column22: A05.EC The company collects, analyses and monitors sex-disaggregated grievance data (e.g. number of grievances reported, number of grievances remediated).
column24: A06.EA The company does employee surveys or other engagement mechanisms that specifically address gender equality & women’s empowerment issues.
column26: A07.EA The company screens for gender-related issues among its suppliers as part of its audit process. Can score Partially Met for .5.
column27: A07.EB The company identifies any gender-related issues as requiring corrective action to be taken by a supplier within a set period of time in order to remediate the issue.
column29: B01.EA The company maintains a gender balance (between 40-60%) at the highest governance body.
column30: B01.EB The company maintains a gender balance (between 40-60%) at the senior executive level.
column31: B01.EC The company maintains a gender balance (between 40-60%) at the senior management level.
column32: B01.ED The company maintains a gender balance (between 40-60%) at the middle/other management level.
column34: B02.EA The company offers professional development programmes (e.g. mentoring programme(s), leadership coaching, access to internal and/or external professional networks, educational programs, and formal sponsorship programmes.
column35: B02.EB The company tracks the number of women who are participating in these programmes.
column37: B03.EA The company collects sex-disaggregated data on the gender balance of its employees by occupational function.
column38: B03.EB The company collects sex-disaggregated data on the percentage of employees promoted.
column39: B03.EC The company collects sex-disaggregated data on the annual turnover of employees.
column40: B03.ED The company collect sex-disaggregated data on the annual absenteeism levels of employees.
column41: B04. Gender equality leadership in the supply chain
column42: B04.EA The company collects or requires its suppliers to collect sex-disaggregated data by leadership level across the supply chain.
column43: B06. Enabling environment for freedom of association and collective bargaining
column44: B06.EB The company describes how it supports the practices of its business relationships in relation to freedom of association and collective bargaining.
column46: B07.EA The company made a public commitment to gender-responsive procurement.
column47: B07.EB The company procures from women-owned businesses.
column49: C01.EA The company collects sex-disaggregated pay data.
column50: C01.EB The company collects sex-disaggregated pay data by different pay bands, occupational functions, or other financial benefits.
column51: C01.EC The company uses a third party to undertake/verify its pay gap analysis.
column52: C02. Paid primary and secondary carer leave
column53: C02.EA The company has a global policy of providing at least 14 weeks of paid primary carer leave offered to full-time employees.
column54: C02.EB The company monitors the return-to-work rate of employees after primary carer leave and their retention a year after primary carer leave.
column55: C02.EC The company has a global policy of providing at least two weeks of paid secondary carer leave offered to full-time employees.
column56: C02.ED The company tracks the number of workers who take secondary carer leave.
column57: C03. Childcare and other family support
column58: C03.EA The company offers childcare support to employees.
column59: C03.EB The company offers other family support to its employees.
column61: C04.EA The company offers flexible working hours to its employees (the ability to alter the start and end of the day).
column62: C04.EB The company collects sex-disaggregated data on the number of employees who have flexible working hour arrangements.
column63: C04.EC The company offers flexible work locations to its employees (the ability to work from home/telecommuting).
column64: C04.ED The company collects sex-disaggregated data on the number of employees who have flexible work location arrangements.
column65: C06. Living wage in the supply chain
column66: C06.EA The company requires its suppliers to pay their workers a living wage.
column67: C06.EB The company takes specific actions to help ensure its suppliers pay their workers a living wage.
column68: D01. Health, safety and well-being in the workplace
column69: D01.EA The company has a publicly available policy statement committing it to respect the health and safety of its employees.
column70: D01.EB The company discloses sex-disaggregated information on health and safety for its employees.
column71: D01.EC The company provides coverage of the costs associated with any of the following health information and services: maternal health, sexual and reproductive health, and mental health. It has to provide more than two different services for a full score. Partially met if only one service is provided.
column72: D02. Safe and healthy work in the supply chain
column73: D02.EA The company has a publicly available statement of policy that expects its business relationships to commit to respecting the health and safety of their workers.
column74: D02.EC The company discloses how it monitors the health and safety performance of its business relationships.
column76: E01.EA The company has publicly available policies in place regarding violence and harassment in the workplace (e.g., zero tolerance policy, safe transport policy, etc.). Can score Partially Met for .5.
column78: E02.EA The company has a remediation process for addressing violence and harassment grievances in the workplace. Can score Partially Met for .5.
column79: E02.EB The company collects, analyses and monitors sex-disaggregated data on the remediation of violence and harassment grievances.
